Sysfs Virtual Flag Toggle Kernel Module
  Description

This Linux kernel module demonstrates how to create a sysfs interface that allows user-space applications to interact with a virtual flag variable inside the kernel.

The module creates a directory /sys/kernel/virtual_flag/ with a file enabled.

Users can read or write to this file to toggle the virtual flag.

Skills Covered

Working with kobject and sysfs_create_file()

Reading/writing to sysfs attributes

User-to-kernel data exchange via sysfs
